      ╚═╝░░░░░╚═╝░░░╚═╝░░░  ╚═╝░░░░░╚═╝╚═╝░░╚═╝╚═╝░░╚═╝╚═╝░░╚═╝╚══════╝░░░╚═╝░░░  ╚═╝░░╚═╝╚═╝░░░░░╚═╝░░░░░
""")
print("Please select following options")

# We need to know number of item from user
Item_Num = int(input("please Enter numbers of Item : "))

# we create a list of basket and money
basket = []
Money_pay = []

# if user entered number of Number of items is "less than 1"
# will print("Seems like you 're not in the mood for shopping today")
# else : program will RUN
if Item_Num >= 0:
  for x in range(1, Item_Num + 1):
    # Ask user to enter item name
    Item_Name = input(f"Please tell me the name of item {x}:\n")
    # Add to the List of basket
    basket.append(Item_Name)
    # Ask user the price of Item
    Price = float(input(f"Please tell me the price of item {x}:\n"))
    # Add price to the list of Money_pay to calculate the total
    Money_pay.append(Price)
  basket_item = input("DO You want to see your entrise basket items ? (Yes/No): ")
  if basket_item.upper() == "YES":
    print(f"Your basket items are {basket}")
  elif basket_item.lower() == "no":
    input("press Enter to Exit")
  else:
    print("Invalid Input Please try again")
  Money_info = input("DO You want to see how much it'll cost ? (Yes/No): ")
  if Money_info.upper() == "YES":
    print(f"Buying These Items will cost {sum(Money_pay)} $")
  elif Money_info.lower() == "no":
    input("press Enter to Exit")
  else:
    print("Invalid Input Please try again")
else:
  print("Seems like you're not in the mood for shopping today'")











